The paper deals with security properties of computer architectures, specifically caches, and proposes a novel model for quantifying these properties. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the interplay between security and efficiency, which could also place it in the cs.AR (Architecture) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and static analyzers, which could indicate a connection to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with computer systems and their components, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
